                    <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">It has been rightly said that while knowledge without application is simply knowledge, applying that knowledge in our daily lives is wisdom and this is the driving force behind the  Investigative Sciences module. Last month, we learnt about the steps of the Scientific  Method, identifying different variables in our experiments and the process of writing a Lab  Report. And in the last two weeks, we have been applying that knowledge via a series  of entertaining experiments, ranging from <strong> shadow puppets</strong> to<strong>exploding watermelons</strong>. </p>
    
                
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Our first experiment was simulation based, where we picked topics that pique our individual  interests and conducted our own experiments based on them.  </p>

