            </div>

            <div class="col-md-12">
                <p class="sub-title pad-bt15">Finally, we had the most exciting experiment of the term - exploding watermelons. The idea  behind this experiment was to find out how many rubber-bands were needed to be put around a  watermelon for it to explode. A few unfortunate students were on the receiving end of the  watermelon's fury but most of us escaped unscathed. 
                    The Investigative Science module is one of the most enjoyable modules because we learn by  applying our knowledge through a variety of experiments. If you hear the buzz of excited students coming from an IB lab, you are likely to have stumbled into another one of our ongoing Investigative Sciences classes, where we have been working on an experiment to apply what we had learnt. </p>

